text.section:
If the register finds that the petition and additional information filed in the proceeding is accurate, he shall:
Direct that the petitioner serve as personal representative of the small estate and issue additional letters of administration as needed;
Direct the immediate payment of the allowable funeral expenses as provided in § 8-106 of this article and the family allowances provided in § 3-201 of this article;
Direct sale of property as may be necessary to satisfy expenses and allowances; and
If it appears that there will be property remaining after the payments, expenses and allowances, admit a will to probate and direct that notice be given in accordance with subsection (b) of this section.
